children.subject:
Hi,

I believe in CalCentral under your schedule of classes there should be options to click "Add," "Drop", "Options," etc. 

If you click "Options" I think you can change just your discussion or lab times without unenrolling from the class, assuming the change you're trying to make is possible- even then you can just cancel out of it with no problems. I'm not a 100% sure, as I don't want you to get waitlisted from wrong information, but I did it often during the Phases. Good luck!

history.content: I am taking 16A next semester but the lab time is clashing with one of my classes how can I switch labs? Can someone help me out with that. When I go to switch classes it is switching the entire class and I am afraid if I do that I will be wait listed. I just want to switch my lab.
history.subject: Switching labs in 16A
